@startuml 05-deployment
title Forge — Diagrama de Implantação

skinparam shadowing false

cloud "Telegram\nBot API" as TG

node "Máquina do operador (Linux/macOS/Windows)" as Host {

  node "Shell (bash/zsh/pwsh)" as Shell {
    artifact "Launcher `forge`\n(função injetada no\n~/.bashrc / ~/.zshrc)" as Launcher
  }

  node "Processo Claude Code\n(CLI)" as CC {
    component "Kernel" as Kern
    component "Subagentes\n(PO, TL, Dev, QA)" as Sub
    component "Skills\n(configure, access)" as Sk
  }

  node "Processo server.ts\n(Bun — MCP stdio)" as Srv {
    component "grammy bot" as G
    component "MCP tools" as MT
    component "gate / handlers" as GH
  }

  folder "~/.claude/" as Home {
    folder "channels/<nome>/" as Ch {
      file ".env (chmod 600)" as EnvF
      file "access.json" as Acc
      file "mode" as Md
      file "bot.pid" as Pid
      folder "approved/" as Ap
      folder "inbox/" as In
    }
    file "settings.json\n(allowlist Forge tools)" as Set
    folder "plugins/forge/\n(server.ts, agents/, skills/)" as Plug
  }

  node "Repositório de trabalho\n(working directory)" as Repo {
    file "CLAUDE.md" as CMD
    file "código-fonte + .git" as Code
  }
}

Launcher --> CC : exec claude\n+ FORGE_CHANNEL=<n>\n+ permission-mode
CC <--> Srv : stdio (MCP)
Srv <--> TG : HTTPS long polling
Srv --> Ch : lê/escreve estado
CC --> Set : carrega permissões
CC --> Plug : carrega plugin
Sub --> Repo : lê/edita código,\ngit commit
Sk --> Ch : configura canais
Sk --> Set : adiciona allowlist

note right of Srv
  1 processo por canal.
  bot.pid evita 409 Conflict
  (só um poller por token).
end note

note right of Launcher
  Se mode=edit →
    --permission-mode bypassPermissions
  Senão → modo padrão (ask).
end note

@enduml
